going to hide those top "2 layers" and play

00:01:41.619 --> 00:01:46.689
around with the first layer, so for the "first
layer" we are just going to bring the "opacity"

00:01:46.689 --> 00:01:55.400
to around about "32%" and all we really want
to do is just bring down the skin tone just

00:01:55.420 --> 00:02:01.039
so she is pale but not to much that the colour
is going to much out of it, now once we have

00:02:01.039 --> 00:02:09.700
done that we are going to bring on the next
layer, click that and we are going to bring

00:02:09.789 --> 00:02:15.450
the "blending mode" to "screen" and this really brightens the image up but it has brightened

00:02:15.450 --> 00:02:23.600
it to much so we are going to bring the "opacity" to around about "20%" but as I said play around

00:02:23.660 --> 00:02:29.220
